               <msContents>
                  <summary>F<locus target="#1r">fols. 1r, </locus>-6v: Prayer, “For the sake of peaceful holy things,”Bä’ǝntä Qǝdsat, በእንተ፡ ቅድሳት፡ ሰላማዊት፡. MQ 26 –9; MG 41ff.; Liturgy 33 –7. F<locus target="#6v">6v, </locus> and passim, mention the owner, ኃይለ ሥላሴ. F<locus target="#6v">6v, </locus>-8v: Prayer, በሰማይ የሀሉ ልብክሙ,  from the Anaphora of Our Lord. F<locus target="#8v">8v, </locus>-17v: Prayer, እግዚአብሔር ዘብርሃናት. F<locus target="#17v">17v, </locus>-19v: Prayer, ፍትሐተ ማይ. F<locus target="#19v">19v, </locus>-34r: Prayer, ነአኵተከ አምላክ ቅዱስ, from the Anaphora of Our Lord with the remainder of the Anaphora. F<locus target="#34r">34r, </locus>-39v: Prayer, Praise of the Beloved for Mary, from Horologium for the Night Hours.  F<locus target="#40r">40r, </locus>-42v: Prayer, Praise of the Beloved for Mary and her Son Together. F<locus target="#45r">45r, </locus>-66r: Chants called Kǝśtät, ክሥተት፡.  Arranged for the days of the week: Wednesday (<locus target="#54v">54v, </locus>), Thursday (<locus target="#57v">57v, </locus>), Friday (<locus target="#59r">59r, </locus>),  Saturday (<locus target="#60r">60r, </locus>). F<locus target="#67r">67r, </locus>-72v: Asmat prayer spoken to Andrew, EMIP 247. Incipit: በስመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ . . . ጸሎት፡ ዘተናገሮ፡ ለእንደርያስ፡ ሐዋርያ፡ ጸሎቱ፡ . . .  <locus target="#72v">72v, </locus> mentions the scribe, ኃይለ ማርያም. <locus target="#75r">75r</locus> has a pen trail in form of a prayer, "Bless my pen; make it a good writing pen."</summary>

